cff-version: 1.2.0

title: Dissent

message: >
  If you use Dissent in research,
  publications, products, or derivative work,
  please cite the original project.

authors:
  - family-names: "Jain"
    given-names: "Dravvya"

repository-code: "https://github.com/dravv-alt/Dissent"

abstract: >
  Dissent is the original open-source framework for detecting,
  explaining, and counteracting AI sycophantic behavior through
  transparent, evidence-based behavioral analysis. It operates
  through a six-layer intervention pipeline including truthfulness
  contracts, epistemic interception, position tracking, response
  detection, counter-prompt intervention, and social validation
  analysis — all with a strict zero-exfiltration privacy model.

keywords:
  - ai-safety
  - sycophancy
  - explainable-ai
  - browser-extension
  - llm
  - behavioral-auditing
  - chatgpt
  - claude
  - gemini

license: Apache-2.0

date-released: "2026-05-01"
